               <p>ROSETTA COHEN. I was twelve years old last January. On the 7th of May I was in <placeName id="t18270531-286-crimeloc1540">York-street, Stepney</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-286-crimeloc1540" type="placeName" value="York-street, Stepney"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-286-crimeloc1540" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-286-off1538 t18270531-286-crimeloc1540"></join>, and stopped to look at Punch and Judy. I saw the prisoner following me, whichever way I went. I had seen him on the Friday night before, in Whitechapel, but had no quarrel with him - I said nothing to him; I did not see him do any thing - but Smith came and took me into a hairdresser's shop, and told me to feel my pocket and see if I had lost any thing. I found my pelisse was cut as if with a knife - I lost nothing; I had a silver thimble and pencil there.</p>
               <p>HYAM BENJAMIN COHEN. This child is my daughter, and resides with me - a gentleman called and took me to York-street; I found her in a hair-dresser's shop with her pelisse cut.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-286-person1564">
                  HENRY 
                  WHITFIELD
               <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1564" type="surname" value="WHITFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1564" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1564" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 7th of May I was selling shrimps, and saw Rosetta Cohen in the street; I saw the prisoner go up to her, take a knife out of his pocket, and cut her pelisse one way - he then shut his knife, put it into his pocket, and appeared to be stooping to find her pocket-hole; he then took his knife out again and cut it the other way.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-286-person1565">
                  GEORGE 
                  WATSON
               <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1565" type="surname" value="WATSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1565" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1565" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I stood next to the prisoner, and saw him take the knife and cut the girl's pelisse across twice.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-286-person1566">
                  RICHARD 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1566" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1566" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1566" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol. In consequence of what the witnesses told me I came up, and ask the prisoner into custody. I found no knife d</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-286-person1567">
                  HENRY 
                  WHITFIELD
               <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1567" type="surname" value="WHITFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1567" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-286-person1567" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am sure he used of knife - it was a sort of square handled knife.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written defence, stating that he was merely standing to look at the show; and was perfectly innocent.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 18.</p>
